-#Â Variable
- cp = current_page.data

:markdown

    A Middleman blog is made up of several different partials.

    To create the front-end of a blog the following are required, a blog name is
    required to be passed to list, archive and pagination. I prefer to set this
    variable in the front-matter.

    - Template: Article list
    - Molecule: Pagination
    - Molecule: Archive
    - Molecule: Tag Cloud

-# Bootstrap row
.row

    -# Bootstrap column
    .col-md-8.col-sm-8

        -# Article list
        = codeBlender "article-list", "template", { name: cp.blogName, page_articles: page_articles }

        -# Pagination variables
        - prevPage = prev_page ? prev_page : false
        - nextPage = next_page ? next_page : false

        -# Pagination
        = codeBlender "pagination", "molecule", { nextPage: nextPage, prevPage: prevPage, pageNo: page_number, pages: num_pages }

    .col-md-4.col-sm-4

        -# Archive
        = codeBlender "archive", "molecule", { name: cp.blogName }

        -# Tag cloud
        = codeBlender "tag-cloud", "molecule", { name: cp.blogName }
